main event: An unidentified object was detected on radar crossing the screen at 200-0 miles at 1330Z on September 1, 1963.
interesting points: The object was tracked for 15 minutes.
The object's type and size were unknown, but it was estimated to be at high altitude.
The report mentions a CIRVIS (Communication Instructions for Reporting Vital Intelligence Sightings) report being filed.
The location of the sighting was 43-28N 173-50W.
The object was reported as eastbound at a high rate of speed.
